# GitHub Automation

Use `gh` CLI for GitHub operations.

## Common Commands

### Issues
```bash
# Create issue
gh issue create --title "Bug: description" --body "Details" --label bug

# List issues
gh issue list --state open --assignee "@me"

# Close issue
gh issue close 123 --comment "Fixed in #456"
```

### Pull Requests
```bash
# Create PR
gh pr create --title "TICKET-123: description" --body "## Summary" --base main

# List PRs
gh pr list --state open --assignee "@me"

# Merge PR (squash)
gh pr merge 123 --squash --delete-branch

# Review PR
gh pr review 123 --approve
gh pr review 123 --request-changes --body "issue: Fix X"
```

### Repositories
```bash
# Clone
gh repo clone owner/repo

# List repos
gh repo list --limit 50

# Create repo
gh repo create name --private --clone
```

### Workflows (Actions)
```bash
# List workflows
gh workflow list

# Run workflow
gh workflow run ci.yml --ref main

# View run status
gh run list --workflow ci.yml
gh run view 12345
```

### Multiple Accounts
```bash
# Switch account
gh auth switch -u USERNAME

# Check current
gh auth status
```

## Best Practices
- Include ticket ID in PR titles: `TICKET-123: description`
- Use `--squash` merge for clean history
- Reference issues in commits: `Fixes #123`
